content:
I do not know that we have much to discuss.

Jobserver work: Cargo patch landed, rustc patch is now in progress. There's a potential concern of Alex's to highlight around sccache and the new jobserver protocol, but I don't know that we need to discuss it...
@Alex Crichton do you have thoughts re:sccache change?
@simulacrum I'm back from vacations but kind of lost on the current state of things and tasks
is there something where I can help or something that you suggest me to check to catch up?
I am not sure. I think we're somewhat up in the air broadly speaking, not quite clear that we're tracking any specific initiatives.
maybe if there's any task where I can help I can just jump in ...
otherwise I will try to check logs to get some context and then in the next meeting we can see what can I do

@simulacrum honestly I'm not sure, if I had to guess the way this will work is that cargo will keep the flag you added, but stabilize it, and eventually sxcache will need to parse way more from rustc as cargo does
do we have anything to meet about?
Prolly not then if you don't have much, I can review the rustc patch today too but on my own time
sure, yeah, no rush of course (mostly open questions, not too many changes)
@WG-parallel-rustc does anyone have agenda items for us today?
